This paper deals with the process of refactoring legacy JavaScript code to adopt the new syntax for classes introduced by ES6. This involves analyzing the code and applying a set of migration rules. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with programming languages and their evolution, which makes it relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also involves collecting perceptions of JavaScript developers, which could fall under the Learning (cs.LG) or Other (cs.OH) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with refactoring and improving code, which could also be relevant to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
